Slpkg is a feature-rich package manager for Slackware-based systems.
It installs, upgrades, removes, and builds packages from multiple
repositories, including SlackBuilds.org (SBo, Ponce) and binary repositories.
Slpkg automatically resolves and tracks dependencies, maintains a full
installation history with transaction rollback, detects orphaned and
foreign packages, and verifies the integrity of installed files.

Additional features include reverse dependency analysis, package
pinning and blacklisting, security auditing, file search within
package indexes, and export/import of package lists.

The tool follows the standards of the SlackBuilds.org organization and
Slackware Linux's official procedures for package installation,
upgrades, and removal.

Optional dependency:
  python3-pythondialog alternatives for dependency and package management.

